WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.460
Oxford Bookworms, Stage 1. A Ghost in Love

00:04.460 --> 00:06.440
and Other Plays by Michael Dean.

00:07.320 --> 00:11.040
Published and Copyright Oxford University Press 2007.

00:14.280 --> 00:16.760
One Ghost for the Day, One Ghost for

00:16.760 --> 00:17.140
the Night.

00:18.200 --> 00:23.720
Performed by Ben Elliott, Lawrence Kennedy, Sarem Arthland,

00:24.560 --> 00:27.340
Coraline Sheldon, and Terry Wilton.

00:49.440 --> 00:52.300
One Ghost for the Day, One Ghost for

00:52.300 --> 00:52.640
the Night.

00:53.740 --> 00:57.640
Seen one, a ghost comes to Richard Little.

00:58.980 --> 01:01.780
The year is 1653.

01:02.900 --> 01:05.200
It is a cold, dark winter night.

01:06.000 --> 01:09.240
And Richard Little, a man of forty, is

01:09.240 --> 01:10.200
sitting in his chair.

01:11.180 --> 01:12.380
He is reading a book.

01:13.320 --> 01:14.380
He hears something.

01:15.440 --> 01:18.700
He goes to the window, looks out, and

01:18.700 --> 01:20.340
then goes back to the chair.

01:21.280 --> 01:23.320
His wife Mary comes in.

01:24.200 --> 01:25.420
She is making a dress.

01:25.420 --> 01:29.040
She has the dress in her hand.

01:32.000 --> 01:35.000
Mary, I can hear something outside.

01:36.220 --> 01:37.680
There's nothing there.

01:38.600 --> 01:39.860
Read your book, Richard.

01:41.160 --> 01:42.740
Come and sit with me.

01:43.400 --> 01:45.260
No, I'm making a dress.

01:46.480 --> 01:47.280
I'm going upstairs.

01:48.720 --> 01:49.460
Mary, please.

01:50.700 --> 01:52.140
There's something out there.

01:52.140 --> 01:53.600
Oh, Richard.

01:56.940 --> 01:58.460
Hello, Richard.

01:59.200 --> 01:59.600
Ah!

02:00.800 --> 02:01.460
You!

02:02.600 --> 02:03.140
James!

02:04.800 --> 02:05.680
James Heston!

02:06.960 --> 02:09.400
But you... you are dead.

02:09.840 --> 02:10.120
Yes.

02:10.960 --> 02:11.980
I am dead.

02:12.840 --> 02:15.220
But I can't find peace because of you.

02:15.960 --> 02:16.860
Because of me.

02:17.980 --> 02:18.580
Why?

02:18.580 --> 02:21.100
Why because of me?

02:21.940 --> 02:24.460
Beth had a new husband after me.

02:25.200 --> 02:27.320
That animal, Keach.

02:27.760 --> 02:28.280
Yes.

02:29.260 --> 02:31.960
Beth was a good woman and a good

02:31.960 --> 02:32.760
sister to me.

02:33.700 --> 02:36.040
I said to her, don't go with Keach.

02:36.720 --> 02:37.440
Think of James.

02:38.400 --> 02:39.300
He's dead now.

02:40.120 --> 02:43.700
She was Keach's wife for only three months.

02:44.700 --> 02:45.680
Then she died.

02:45.680 --> 02:49.060
And now Keach has my son.

02:49.660 --> 02:52.200
And he has my son's money.

02:53.120 --> 02:53.480
Ah!

02:54.300 --> 02:56.300
I understand now.

02:56.700 --> 02:57.060
Oh!

02:57.920 --> 02:59.180
You remember now.

02:59.940 --> 03:03.600
Before I died, I said to you,

03:04.360 --> 03:07.460
my boy gets my money at twenty-one

03:07.460 --> 03:08.980
and not before.

03:09.760 --> 03:11.540
He is eight now.

03:12.240 --> 03:12.740
Eight.

03:13.460 --> 03:15.740
And Keach has his money.

03:16.780 --> 03:18.220
I'm sorry about that.

03:18.920 --> 03:20.180
But what can I do?

03:20.940 --> 03:23.640
You must get my boy's money.

03:24.420 --> 03:25.840
Get it from Keach.

03:26.260 --> 03:26.640
No.

03:27.620 --> 03:29.600
Keach can kill me with one hand.

03:30.320 --> 03:30.700
He's big.

03:31.540 --> 03:33.180
He always has a knife in his pocket.

03:34.200 --> 03:36.400
Last year he killed a man with that

03:36.400 --> 03:36.700
knife.

03:37.860 --> 03:39.420
I'm afraid of him, James.

03:40.260 --> 03:41.800
Are you afraid of me?

03:41.800 --> 03:42.600
No.

03:43.300 --> 03:43.700
Oh.

03:44.780 --> 03:45.980
Yes, a little.

03:46.740 --> 03:47.400
You're a ghost.

03:48.220 --> 03:49.940
Only a little, eh?

03:50.560 --> 03:52.200
Look at the table.

03:52.880 --> 03:53.800
Oh no.

03:54.760 --> 03:55.840
The table is moving.

03:56.840 --> 03:57.760
Oh no.

03:58.840 --> 03:59.180
Oh.

04:00.200 --> 04:01.840
The chair is moving now.

04:02.760 --> 04:04.880
And now my chair is moving.

04:05.840 --> 04:06.560
James.

04:07.820 --> 04:08.960
Don't do this to me.

04:09.900 --> 04:13.700
At this minute, Keach is building a new

04:13.700 --> 04:15.820
home in a village near here,

04:16.480 --> 04:18.220
with my son's money.

04:18.880 --> 04:19.900
Stop him.

04:20.640 --> 04:21.860
I'm sorry, James.

04:22.780 --> 04:24.520
I can't.

04:25.120 --> 04:27.700
I didn't want.

04:28.800 --> 04:30.900
That was my hand, but...

04:31.780 --> 04:34.840
James, can you get in my head?

04:34.840 --> 04:37.860
Can you tell my hand?

04:39.560 --> 04:41.180
Yes, Richard.

04:42.380 --> 04:45.840
And your answer is going to be yes.

04:46.960 --> 04:50.160
Or you are going to do this again

04:50.160 --> 04:55.220
and again and again and...

05:00.580 --> 05:01.920
I'm going mad.

05:02.920 --> 05:05.400
Why does my hand throw a book when

05:05.400 --> 05:06.380
I don't want to?

05:07.660 --> 05:10.620
Can all dead people do this?

05:11.660 --> 05:14.280
Can they get into man's head so he

05:14.280 --> 05:16.160
moves a chair or throws a book?

05:16.620 --> 05:17.820
Oh yes.

05:18.720 --> 05:22.120
Now, I can do it to you again.

05:22.900 --> 05:26.140
Or you can say yes and get my

05:26.140 --> 05:27.280
son's money.

05:27.980 --> 05:28.320
Which?

05:29.320 --> 05:30.160
But how?

05:31.040 --> 05:34.020
How can I get the money from Keach?

05:34.480 --> 05:35.280
Sit down.

05:36.200 --> 05:37.820
I'm going to tell you.

05:41.180 --> 05:42.000
Scene two.

05:43.300 --> 05:44.360
David Keach in court.

05:45.420 --> 05:48.400
In the court we can see Judge Tim's,

05:48.840 --> 05:53.400
Keach, Barker, Reynolds, Richard and Mary.

05:54.240 --> 05:57.560
There are six women and six men behind

05:57.560 --> 05:58.160
Keach.

05:58.680 --> 06:01.080
They are from the village and they are

06:01.080 --> 06:01.960
watching the trial.

06:03.040 --> 06:05.500
Judge Tim's is in a big chair in

06:05.500 --> 06:06.320
front of the court.

06:09.980 --> 06:14.600
My name is Oliver Barker and I speak

06:14.600 --> 06:17.180
for Richard Little here today.

06:18.740 --> 06:20.100
Judge Tim's.

06:20.680 --> 06:23.160
I speak for David Keach here today.

06:23.820 --> 06:25.540
My name is Philip Reynolds.

06:26.260 --> 06:28.200
That Keach took the boy's money.

06:28.720 --> 06:30.240
You can see it in his face.

06:30.880 --> 06:31.380
Oh, Lil.

06:32.100 --> 06:34.340
We must listen to Oliver Barker and Philip

06:34.340 --> 06:35.420
Reynolds first.

06:36.560 --> 06:38.880
Keach is the boy Tom's father now.

06:39.720 --> 06:42.900
A good father doesn't take his son's money

06:42.900 --> 06:45.140
and build a new house with it.

06:45.140 --> 06:47.260
Be quiet in my court.

06:47.480 --> 06:48.000
Sorry.

06:48.760 --> 06:50.040
Oliver Barker.

06:50.860 --> 06:51.580
You can begin.

06:52.640 --> 06:54.240
Judge Tim's.

06:55.200 --> 06:59.360
Before James Heston died, he said this to

06:59.360 --> 06:59.980
Richard Little.

07:00.760 --> 07:03.880
He said, my boy gets my money at

07:03.880 --> 07:05.760
21 and not before.

07:06.260 --> 07:09.320
At 21 and not before.

07:10.300 --> 07:11.240
Yes, Judge.

07:12.420 --> 07:15.120
But Keach has this money now.

07:15.800 --> 07:16.820
The boy's money.

07:17.600 --> 07:20.220
He is building a big house with it.

07:20.820 --> 07:22.060
We all know that.

07:22.560 --> 07:24.580
Put Keach in prison, I say.

07:25.980 --> 07:26.980
Five years.

07:27.580 --> 07:28.000
No.

07:28.520 --> 07:28.780
Ten.

07:29.460 --> 07:29.860
You.

07:30.520 --> 07:31.900
Don't eat in my court.

07:33.200 --> 07:33.940
Philip Reynolds.

07:35.080 --> 07:35.200
Speak.

07:36.280 --> 07:37.480
Judge Tim's.

07:37.840 --> 07:39.920
Yes, there is a house in a village

07:39.920 --> 07:40.580
near here.

07:40.580 --> 07:42.840
And yes, it is Keach's house.

07:43.500 --> 07:46.220
But the money for it is not young

07:46.220 --> 07:47.220
Tom's money.

07:47.640 --> 07:50.140
Not Tom's money.

07:50.700 --> 07:52.380
No, Judge Tim's.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.620
It is David Keach's money.

07:55.660 --> 07:58.840
So one day Keach is not rich.

07:59.660 --> 08:02.020
And the next day he is rich.

08:02.620 --> 08:04.220
He has money for a house.

08:07.160 --> 08:09.080
Call David Keach.

08:11.180 --> 08:12.420
David Keach.

08:12.880 --> 08:15.000
Where is the boy Tom's money?

08:15.760 --> 08:16.880
Do you have it at home?

08:17.720 --> 08:18.020
No.

08:18.920 --> 08:20.180
Keach took the money.

08:20.560 --> 08:21.600
It was Keach.

08:21.980 --> 08:23.500
I said Keach took the money.

08:23.780 --> 08:24.720
I said that yesterday.

08:25.800 --> 08:27.280
I have the money here.

08:27.820 --> 08:28.460
In this court.

08:28.940 --> 08:30.180
The money here.

08:30.600 --> 08:31.100
Keach didn't teach.

08:31.100 --> 08:31.980
Keach didn't teach.

08:32.440 --> 08:34.460
In this court.

08:35.720 --> 08:37.600
The money is under my chair.

08:38.520 --> 08:38.960
You, woman.

08:39.560 --> 08:40.200
Bring me the money.

08:41.040 --> 08:41.640
Me?

08:42.120 --> 08:42.820
Yes, you.

08:44.980 --> 08:46.020
Here you are.

08:47.160 --> 08:47.760
Here.

08:48.700 --> 08:49.900
Judge Tim's.

08:50.820 --> 08:51.040
Here.

08:51.640 --> 08:52.200
Richard Little.

08:53.220 --> 08:53.660
Here.

08:54.120 --> 08:54.920
Look, everybody.

08:55.900 --> 08:56.800
Here is the money.

08:57.420 --> 08:59.480
So I didn't take it from the boy.

08:59.480 --> 09:01.260
You hear me, Richard Little?

09:01.800 --> 09:02.560
Yes.

09:03.340 --> 09:04.400
One minute.

09:05.200 --> 09:05.960
Richard Little.

09:06.920 --> 09:08.620
Yes, Judge Tim's.

09:09.580 --> 09:13.120
You said Keach took the boy's money.

09:13.780 --> 09:14.580
You said that.

09:15.200 --> 09:15.500
Why?

09:16.380 --> 09:17.040
Why man?

09:17.900 --> 09:18.460
Why?

09:19.660 --> 09:21.420
Why say that?

09:22.900 --> 09:23.780
Because...

09:24.880 --> 09:25.760
Because...

09:25.760 --> 09:28.820
Because James Heston came to my home.

09:29.540 --> 09:31.500
James Heston said it to me.

09:32.040 --> 09:33.060
James Heston?

09:33.060 --> 09:33.780
He said it.

09:33.800 --> 09:35.700
Because James Heston's dead.

09:36.040 --> 09:36.640
Richard Little.

09:37.320 --> 09:39.220
James Heston is dead.

09:40.040 --> 09:42.480
He died in 1651.

09:43.460 --> 09:44.120
He taught with me.

09:44.120 --> 09:44.680
He taught with me.

09:44.840 --> 09:45.300
Oh man.

09:45.440 --> 09:45.720
Oh man.

09:46.480 --> 09:46.800
Oh man.

09:48.380 --> 09:49.400
Judge Tim's.

09:49.740 --> 09:51.080
My husband is ill.

09:51.960 --> 09:52.680
In our house.

09:53.200 --> 09:54.180
He talks to people.

09:54.640 --> 09:55.800
And there is nobody there.

09:56.480 --> 09:58.700
Can I take him home now, please?

10:00.900 --> 10:02.080
I am not ill.

10:02.540 --> 10:03.620
Stop laughing.

10:04.120 --> 10:04.700
Be quiet.

10:04.980 --> 10:05.360
All of you.

10:06.120 --> 10:07.440
Sit down, Mary.

10:09.060 --> 10:09.920
Thank you.

10:11.260 --> 10:13.080
Yes, James Heston is dead.

10:13.880 --> 10:16.500
And yes, James Heston spoke to me.

10:17.320 --> 10:19.480
I want James Heston here.

10:20.200 --> 10:23.200
Now, he can tell you...

10:23.200 --> 10:24.040
He is ill.

10:24.040 --> 10:25.280
He's mad.

10:25.820 --> 10:27.300
Let's listen to him.

10:27.600 --> 10:29.280
Yes, we can listen to him.

10:29.740 --> 10:30.380
Be quiet.

10:31.340 --> 10:32.780
Call James Heston.

10:33.680 --> 10:37.020
I say, call James Heston to this court.

10:37.560 --> 10:39.240
Heston is dead man.

10:40.080 --> 10:41.840
And Richard Little is mad.

10:42.480 --> 10:45.020
Call James Heston.

10:47.360 --> 10:50.040
I am James Heston.

10:50.650 --> 10:53.280
Oh, he's dead.

10:53.600 --> 10:53.880
He's dead.

10:54.240 --> 10:54.900
No.

10:55.780 --> 10:56.460
No.

10:57.220 --> 10:58.020
Oh, please.

10:58.440 --> 10:58.500
No.

10:59.360 --> 11:00.380
It's Heston.

11:01.380 --> 11:03.000
Oh, the brain.

11:03.520 --> 11:05.340
Oh, it's Heston dead.

11:05.600 --> 11:06.700
James Heston.

11:07.840 --> 11:08.380
Is it you?

11:09.180 --> 11:11.420
Did you speak to Richard Little?

11:12.100 --> 11:12.920
Yes.

11:14.040 --> 11:15.400
What did you say?

11:16.520 --> 11:18.240
I told him.

11:18.240 --> 11:21.060
Keech took my boy's money.

11:22.240 --> 11:24.780
And then Keech killed a man in the

11:24.780 --> 11:25.520
next village.

11:26.820 --> 11:28.220
He was a rich man.

11:28.900 --> 11:30.380
Keech took his money.

11:31.400 --> 11:33.040
You see the money now?

11:33.720 --> 11:35.580
Here, in this court.

11:36.260 --> 11:39.420
I can't kill Heston.

11:40.340 --> 11:41.440
Heston is dead.

11:42.320 --> 11:42.680
But you.

11:43.320 --> 11:44.580
You, Richard Little.

11:44.580 --> 11:47.000
You brought me to this court.

11:47.920 --> 11:49.940
I'm going to kill you next.

11:51.000 --> 11:52.000
Stop him.

11:52.760 --> 11:53.600
Stop him.

11:54.260 --> 11:55.480
It was Keech.

11:56.300 --> 11:57.640
Keech took the money.

11:58.040 --> 11:58.940
I said that.

11:59.500 --> 12:01.200
I said Keech took the money.

12:01.660 --> 12:04.340
This court says Keech took the money.

12:05.080 --> 12:06.500
And Keech killed the man.

12:07.280 --> 12:10.180
Now find David Keech and bring him to

12:10.180 --> 12:10.380
me.

12:13.600 --> 12:14.920
Scene three.

12:15.840 --> 12:17.660
Keech finds Richard Little.

12:18.620 --> 12:21.960
Richard is sitting in his chair at home.

12:23.780 --> 12:24.760
What's that?

12:25.720 --> 12:27.260
Can I hear something?

12:29.100 --> 12:29.380
Mary?

12:30.820 --> 12:31.400
Is that you?

12:32.720 --> 12:33.780
Oh no.

12:34.360 --> 12:35.380
It's not James again.

12:36.160 --> 12:37.000
James?

12:38.100 --> 12:38.680
Is that you?

12:41.680 --> 12:43.560
Oh no.

12:44.840 --> 12:46.060
Oh no.

12:46.860 --> 12:48.500
Keech, please.

12:49.460 --> 12:49.760
No.

12:51.340 --> 12:52.560
Oh no.

12:53.740 --> 12:54.420
Not Richard.

12:55.420 --> 12:56.920
Not my darling.

12:57.420 --> 12:58.440
Darling, Richard.

12:59.740 --> 13:01.200
Keech killed him.

13:02.260 --> 13:04.780
You're going to go to prison for this,

13:04.780 --> 13:05.360
Keech.

13:11.400 --> 13:12.440
Scene four.

13:13.240 --> 13:14.880
A visit for Keech in prison.

13:16.300 --> 13:17.580
Keech is in prison.

13:18.560 --> 13:19.720
He is sitting on his bed.

13:20.820 --> 13:23.540
He has a table, a chair, and a

13:23.540 --> 13:24.440
book there too.

13:28.480 --> 13:29.080
Hello?

13:29.680 --> 13:30.360
What's that?

13:31.500 --> 13:32.940
Is there someone there?

13:33.940 --> 13:36.020
My table.

13:36.640 --> 13:38.520
My table is moving.

13:39.560 --> 13:42.340
Now the bed is moving.

13:43.480 --> 13:44.360
Am I ill?

13:45.480 --> 13:47.180
Oh my head.

13:48.680 --> 13:49.360
Oh.

13:50.400 --> 13:52.340
Now the chair is moving.

13:53.820 --> 13:54.700
What's happening?

13:57.540 --> 13:59.000
Why did I do that?

14:00.220 --> 14:01.360
Am I mad?

14:02.700 --> 14:05.120
It was my hand, but...

14:07.240 --> 14:08.200
You're dead.

14:09.020 --> 14:10.220
I killed you.

14:10.760 --> 14:11.280
Yes.

14:12.020 --> 14:12.900
I'm dead.

14:13.800 --> 14:14.880
And you killed me.

14:15.840 --> 14:17.200
But I'm not going away.

14:18.220 --> 14:21.120
I'm staying here in prison with you.

14:22.800 --> 14:24.740
You can't hit me now.

14:25.320 --> 14:26.760
You can't hit a ghost.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.640
And you can't kill me again.

14:30.600 --> 14:31.900
But we can talk.

14:32.680 --> 14:34.220
We have time for that.

14:35.540 --> 14:37.080
We have all day.

14:37.640 --> 14:41.560
And you can do that all day too.

14:42.680 --> 14:43.680
All day?

14:44.560 --> 14:45.360
All the time?

14:45.980 --> 14:46.400
Yes.

14:47.640 --> 14:50.380
Now throw the book across the room again.

14:51.520 --> 14:52.600
And again.

14:52.600 --> 14:54.780
And again.

14:56.100 --> 14:57.400
And again.

14:57.820 --> 14:58.860
Oh no.

14:59.640 --> 15:00.100
Please.

15:01.200 --> 15:03.840
Are all my days going to be like

15:03.840 --> 15:04.120
this?

15:04.480 --> 15:04.960
Your days.

15:05.800 --> 15:06.040
Yes.

15:07.080 --> 15:08.120
And for your nights.

15:08.900 --> 15:10.920
I have a friend here.

15:11.720 --> 15:13.060
Hello Richard.

15:14.120 --> 15:14.960
Hello David.

15:15.380 --> 15:15.620
You.

15:16.260 --> 15:17.760
You here too.

15:18.300 --> 15:18.880
Yes.

15:20.300 --> 15:23.580
David throw the book across the room please.

15:25.160 --> 15:26.200
Thank you.

15:27.120 --> 15:29.820
I'm going to be here at night David.

15:30.600 --> 15:33.400
And you have Richard here every day.

15:34.080 --> 15:34.600
All right.

15:35.180 --> 15:35.920
Oh no.

15:37.060 --> 15:37.600
No.

15:38.420 --> 15:40.400
One ghost for the day.

15:41.440 --> 15:42.820
One ghost for the night.

15:43.740 --> 15:46.840
Now throw the book across the room again.

15:46.840 --> 15:47.020
Then.

15:48.040 --> 15:51.700
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha,

15:52.260 --> 15:52.320
ha.

15:56.700 --> 15:58.300
Sleep Now My Darling.

15:59.280 --> 16:00.800
Performed by Ben Cowan.

16:01.420 --> 16:02.220
Candida Gabbins.

16:02.960 --> 16:03.520
Fiona Molison.

16:04.560 --> 16:04.820
Vince Nichols.

16:05.700 --> 16:06.160
And Chris Rowe.

16:23.360 --> 16:27.880
Sleep Now My Darling. Scene One. Jenny must

16:27.880 --> 16:30.700
stay at home. It is a hot summer

16:30.700 --> 16:32.120
day. Jenny

16:32.120 --> 16:34.260
and Gilbert Lawson are having breakfast at a

16:34.260 --> 16:37.000
table in their garden. Gilbert is reading

16:37.000 --> 16:42.660
a book. Gilbert, can I come with you

